&lt;p>On Linux, the command-line tool &lt;a href="https://github.com/andreafrancia/trash-cli">&lt;code>trash-cli&lt;/code>&lt;/a> provides a &lt;strong>safe alternative to &lt;code>rm&lt;/code>&lt;/strong>, allowing you to move files to the &lt;strong>Trash&lt;/strong> instead of permanently deleting them.&lt;br>
It fully complies with the &lt;a href="https://specifications.freedesktop.org/trash-spec/latest/">FreeDesktop Trash Specification&lt;/a>, which is used by desktop environments such as GNOME and KDE.&lt;/p>
&lt;hr>
